<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Vegan Pizza</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 pizza crust (store-bought or homemade)</li>
            <li>1/2 cup tomato sauce</li>
            <li>1 cup vegan cheese, shredded</li>
            <li>Assorted vegetables (bell peppers, red onions, mushrooms, cherry tomatoes, etc.), sliced</li>
            <li>1/4 cup black olives, sliced</li>
            <li>Fresh basil leaves for garnish</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon olive oil</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon dried oregano</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>Optional: Vegan pepperoni or other plant-based protein toppings</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat your oven according to the pizza crust instructions.</li>
            <li>Roll out the pizza crust on a lightly floured surface and transfer it to a pizza stone or baking sheet.</li>
            <li>Spread a thin layer of tomato sauce over the pizza crust, leaving a small border around the edges.</li>
            <li>Sprinkle vegan cheese evenly over the tomato sauce.</li>
            <li>Add sliced vegetables, black olives, and any optional toppings you prefer.</li>
            <li>Drizzle olive oil over the pizza and sprinkle dried oregano, salt, and black pepper to taste.</li>
            <li>Bake in the preheated oven according to the pizza crust instructions or until the crust is golden and the toppings are cooked.</li>
            <li>Remove from the oven, garnish with fresh basil leaves, and let it cool for a few minutes before slicing.</li>
            <li>Serve your delicious Vegan Pizza hot and enjoy!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

